{"title_page": "National Industrial Security Academy", "text_new": "{{short description|CISF institute}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name                    = National Industrial Security Academy\n| image                   = \n| alt                     = \n| caption                 = \n| motto                   = <!-- or | mottoes = -->\n| motto_translation       = \n| location                = [[Hakimpet]], [[Medchal\u2013Malkajgiri District]], [[Telangana]]\n| country                 = India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|17|32|29|N|78|31|59|E|display=inline.title}}\n| other_name              = <!-- or | other_names = -->\n| former_name             = <!-- or | former_names = -->\n| type                    = Industrial security academy\n| religious_affiliation   = \n| established             = {{Start date|1990|12|08|df=yes}}\n| founder                 = <!-- or | founders = -->\n| closed                  = \n| school_board            = \n| district                = \n| director                = Anjana Sinha, [[Indian Police Service|IPS]]\n| authority               = <!-- or | educational_authority = or | local_authority = -->\n| oversight               = <!-- use | oversight_label = to override the default label -->\n| principal               = <!-- use | principal_label = to override the default label -->\n| head                    = <!-- use | head_label = to override the default label -->\n| staff                   = \n| faculty                 = \n| grades                  = <!-- use | grades_label = to override the default label -->\n| gender                  = <!-- use | gender_label = to override the default label -->\n| age_range               = <!-- or | lower_age = and | upper_age = -->\n| enrollment              = <!-- or | enrolment = or | students = or | pupils = -->\n| enrollment_as_of        = <!-- or | enrolment_as_of = or | students_as_of = or | pupils_as_of = -->\n| medium_of_language      = \n| campus_size             = {{convert|237|acre|ha}}\n| campus_type             = Suburban\n| colors                  = <!-- or | colours = -->\n| teams                   = <!-- use | teams_label = to override the default label -->\n| accreditation           = <!-- or | accreditations = -->\n| publication             = \n| newspaper               = \n| yearbook                = \n| affiliation             = [[Central Industrial Security Force]]\n| website                 = {{website|http://nisa.ap.nic.in/|Official website}}\n| footnotes               = \n}}\n\nThe '''National Industrial Security Academy''' (commonly abbreviated as '''NISA''') is an institution of [[Central Industrial Security Force]] (CISF) for training in [[industrial security]] and [[disaster management]].<ref>{{Cite video |url=https://www.republicworld.com/shows/patriot/patriot-at-cisf-national-industrial-security-academy |title=Patriot at CISF, National Industrial Security Academy \u2014 Part First|language=English, Hindi |publisher=[[Republic TV]] |year=2017|website=Republicworld.com}}</ref> The academy is situated in a {{convert|237|acre|ha|adj=on}} campus at [[Hakimpet]], [[Medchal\u2013Malkajgiri District]], on the outskirts of [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]].\n\nEstablished in 1990 in its present form, the academy imparts basic induction training to the directly recruited and promoted through departmental examinations [[assistant commandant]]s and [[sub-inspector]]s, as well as provides professional and specialised courses for the personnel of CISF, other [[Central Armed Police Forces]], state police, and [[public sector undertakings in India]].<ref name=\"About Us\">{{ cite web | url = http://nisa.ap.nic.in/AboutUs.htm | title = NISA \u2013 About Us | access-date = 12 August 2019 | website = Nisa.ap.nic.in | publisher = National Industrial Security Academy}}</ref> NISA is headed by an [[Inspector General]]-rank officer, designated as the director; this post is currently held by [[Anjana Sinha]], an [[Indian Police Service]] officer from Andhra Pradesh-cadre. The academy has been recognised as the [[centre of excellence]] in industrial security management by the [[Government of India]].<ref name=\"Excellence\">{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/hyderabad/Sub-inspectors-undergo-rigourous-training/articleshow/254486.cms |title=Sub-inspectors undergo rigourous[sic] training |date=28 October 2003 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=19 August 2019|location=Hyderabad}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nCentral Industrial Security Force was established by the Government of India in 1969 to provide security and protection to vital [[state-owned enterprises]]. The CISF Training College came into existence the same year at [[Partapur, Uttar Pradesh|Partapur]], [[Meerut District]], [[Uttar Pradesh]]. Two years later, in 1971, the college was shifted to [[Shivrampalli]], [[Ranga Reddy District]] of [[Andhra Pradesh Reorganisation Act, 2014|undivided]] [[Andhra Pradesh]]. In 1987 the college was transferred to its present campus in Hakimpet village of Ranga Reddy District, which now falls in the Medchal\u2013Malkajgiri District of Telangana. The college was transformed into an academy on 8 December 1990.<ref name=\"About Us\" />\n\n== Training ==\n[[File:CISF subinspector trainees at jungle camp in NISA .jpg|left|thumb|Sub-inspector under trainees during training at NISA]]\nThe Training Sector of Central Industrial Security Force comprises NISA as the academy, the Fire Service Training Institute (FSTI) within the campus of NISA, and six Recruit Training Centres.<ref name=\"Training Sector\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cisf.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/TS_Directory.pdf |title=Training Sector Directory |website=Cisf.gov.in |access-date=18 August 2019|publisher=Central Industrial Security Force}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.theweekendleader.com/Headlines/9083/20-000-troopers-to-enhance-cisf-strength.html |title=20,000 troopers to enhance CISF strength |last=Singh |first=Rajnish |date=13 February 2017 |work=The Weekend Leader |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref> The Sector is headed by an Inspector General-rank officer who also serves in the capacity of director of NISA. Anjana Sinha, an Indian Police Service officer from Andhra Pradesh-cadre, currently holds the position since her deputation to the [[Government of India|Centre]].<ref name=\"NALSAR\">{{Cite news |url=https://telanganatoday.com/nalsar-and-cisf-nisa-award-pg-diplomas-students |title=Nalsar and CISF-NISA award PG diplomas to students |date=7 January 2019 |work=[[Telangana Today]] |access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ips.gov.in/Empanelment/AnjanaSinha_15022018.PDF |title=Appointment of Ms. Anjana Sinha, IPS (AP: 90) as Inspector General in CISF on deputation basis |date=15 February 2018 |website=Ips.gov.in |access-date=18 August 2019|publisher=[[Ministry of Home Affairs (India)|Ministry of Home Affairs]]}}</ref> She assumed charge as director on 18 April 2018 after joining CISF on 2 April.<ref name=\"News Letter\">{{Cite web |url=http://nisa.gov.in/LATESTNEWS/NISA%20NEWS/2018/nisa%20news%20jan_june%202018.pdf |title=NISA Welcomes New Director |publisher=National Industrial Security Academy |page=5 |access-date=18 August 2019|work=NISA News}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 May 2016 at New Delhi, during the [[National Symposium on Excellence in Training]] (NSET),  NISA received a national award for 'excellence in training' in the category of trainer and faculty development. The Symposium is organised by the [[Department of Personnel and Training]], and NISA was the sole awardee in 2016.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/cisf-s-hyderabad-based-academy-gets-national-training-award-116053001431_1.html |title=CISF's Hyderabad-based academy gets national training award |date=30 May 2016 |work=[[Business Standard]] |access-date=19 August 2019 | agency=[[Press Trust of India]]}}</ref>\n\n== Securitypedia ==\nSecuritypedia is an online encyclopedia of CISF developed and maintained by the research and development wing of the Technical Laboratory (TechLab) of NISA. Currently it is available only to CISF personnel through the employee web portal and mobile application EmpPower. However, the platform is envisioned to be made available to other [[Central Armed Police Force]]s in future. It contains articles related to security technologies including gadgets, CISF units, study material used by CISF trainees and articles on other various national and international law enforcement agencies. The encyclopedia is based on [[Wikipedia]] in a way that it allows its readers to edit articles after providing reliable and verifiable references but new articles can only be published after the scrutiny of the TechLab which is operated by a staff of CISF officers with technical background academically.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/cisf-launches-youtube-wikipedia-portals-train-forces-securitypedia-5853233/ |title=With personnel spending more time on phones, CISF launches YouTube, Wikipedia like portals to train forces |date=26 July 2019 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |access-date=26 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Trivedi |first=Saurabh |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/cisf-launches-encyclopaedia-to-strengthen-security-services/article28734396.ece |title=CISF launches encyclopaedia to strengthen security services  |date=28 July 2019 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=26 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Campus ==\nA {{convert|237|acre|ha}} suburban campus of the academy is situated in [[Hakimpet]] village of Medchal\u2013Malkajgiri district, Telangana, on the periphery of Hyderabad city. It includes a hostel for officers trainees, three hostels for subordinate officers trainees, suites for [[flag officers]], and barracks with capacity for 600 personnel. There is a language laboratory and training module based on the [[learning management system]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://nisa.ap.nic.in/Trg_Facilities2.php |title=Training Facilities |access-date=19 August 2019|website=Nisa.ap.nic.in|publisher=National Industrial Security Academy}}</ref>\n\nThe Martyr's Memorial of CISF is located at the NISA campus. This memorial honours the personnel who have lost their lives serving for the force since 1969.<ref>{{Cite video |url=https://www.republicworld.com/shows/patriot/patriot-at-cisf-part-2 |title=Patriot at CISF, National Industrial Security Academy \u2014 Part Second |language=English, Hindi |publisher=[[Republic TV]] |year=2017 | website=Republicworld.com | access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Courses conducted ==\n[[File:Rajnath Singh inspecting the guard of honour at the Passing Out Parade of 29th Battalion of Assistant Commandants and 41st Batch of Sub-Inspectors of Central Industrial Security Force.jpg|right|thumb|[[Rajnath Singh]] inspecting the guard of honour at the Passing Out Parade of the 29th batch of Assistant Commandants and 41st Batch of Sub-Inspectors at NISA]] \nThe academy conducts different basic and promotion courses for gazetted and subordinate officers, basic courses for assistant commandants recruited through direct appointment and departmental entry, sub-inspectors executive and sub-inspectors fire through direct appointment, and promotion courses of all the gazetted ranks up to inspector general. Promotion courses of inspector executive to assistant commandant executive and inspectors, both ministerial and stenographer, to assistant commandant junior accounts officer, are also held at NISA.<ref name=\"Courses\">{{Cite web |url=http://nisa.ap.nic.in/Courses%20and%20other%20files/FOR%20TEC%20CENTRE/Cources%20at%20NISA.pdf | title=Courses at NISA | website=Nisa.ap.nic.in |access-date=13 August 2019 | publisher=National Industrial Security Academy}}</ref> After the completion of training at NISA, assistant commandants and sub-inspectors are also awarded a postgraduate diploma in industrial security, law and management recognised by [[NALSAR University of Law]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://telanganatoday.com/nalsar-and-cisf-nisa-award-pg-diplomas-students |title=Nalsar and CISF-NISA award PG diplomas to students |date=7 January 2019 |work=[[Telangana Today]] |access-date=26 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nTwenty-eight specialised outdoor and indoor courses and workshops are carried out by the academy; the [[Krav Maga]] and [[Parkour]] Trainer of Trainees Course for the subordinate officers and the other ranks are of the longest duration, spanning five weeks.<ref name=\"Courses\" />\n\nNISA conducts courses for other organisations as well; these include a three-week training course for [[Indian Revenue Service]] probationers, a disaster management course for district level officers, a critical incident management course for gazetted officers, a capsule course on installation security [[intrusion detection system]] and [[improvised explosive device]]s, and junior-level (for subordinate officers) and senior-level (for gazetted officers up to the rank of deputy commandant) industrial security courses. A five-day seminar on industrial security is also held at the academy.<ref name=\"Courses\" />\n\n== Training to other organisations ==\nNISA also provides training to the personnel of different security agencies and police organisations.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-soon-elite-force-for-metro-security-2559597 |title=Soon, elite force for Metro security |last=Srivastava |first=Anvit |date=13 November 2017 |work=[[Daily News and Analysis]] |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref> [[Karnataka]] instated a special industrial security force \u2013 Karnataka State Industrial Security Force \u2013 along the lines of CISF, and training to its 139 sub-inspectors was carried out at NISA in a nine-month-long training programme in 2013.<ref name=\"KSISF\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.deccanherald.com/content/323410/states-own-industrial-security-force.html |title=State's own industrial security force taking shape |last=Kumar |first=Chethan |date=3 April 2013 |work=[[Deccan Herald]] |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref> A delegation of the Ministry of Interior, [[Government of Qatar]], expressed its interest for the Qatar's industrial security force personnel deployed for providing security to the oil and gas installations of the country to be trained at NISA after meeting with the officials of CISF, including the [[Director General]] [[Rajesh Ranjan (IPS officer)|Rajesh Ranjan]], on 19 November 2018 at its headquarters in New Delhi.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/qatar-keen-on-cisf-training-for-its-industrial-security-force-118111901440_1.html |title=Qatar keen on CISF training for its industrial security force |date=19 November 2018 |work=[[Business Standard]] |access-date=19 August 2018|agency=[[Indo-Asian News Service]]|location=New Delhi}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/headlines/259714-qatar-wants-cisf-training-for-its-industrial-security-force |title=Qatar wants CISF training for its industrial security force |date=19 November 2018 |website=Devdiscourse.com |access-date=19 August 2019|location=New Delhi}}</ref>\n\n== CISF Golden Jubilee Walkathon ==\nA {{convert|5|km|mi|adj=on}} long [[walkathon]] was oragnised by the academy on 6 January 2019 to mark the golden jubilee year of the formation of CISF and to create awareness on good health, fitness and security. With a slogan of \"let's walk together to make India secure\", the wakathon was flagged-off at People's Plaza, [[Necklace Road]], by Indian cricketer and the captain of the [[Indian women's national cricket team]] [[Mithali Raj]] in the presence of [[Telugu cinema|Telugu actor]] [[Sumanth]], [[Dronacharya Award]]-winner athletic coach Nagapuri Ramesh, Telangana State Municipal Administration and Urban Development Department principal secretary Arvind Kumar and [[Hyderabad City Police|Hyderabad Commissioner of Police]] [[Anjani Kumar]]. Besides several CISF officers and personnel, participants were also included from other Central Armed Police Forces, Hyderabad City Police and civilians.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://telanganatoday.com/cisf-holds-golden-jubilee-year-walkathon |title=CISF holds Golden Jubilee Year Walkathon |date=6 January 2019 |work=[[Telangana Today]] |access-date=26 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/walkathon-organised-in-hyderabad-to-mark-cisf-golden-jubilee/1434863/ |title=Walkathon organised in Hyderabad to mark CISF golden jubilee |date=6 January 2019 |work=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]] |access-date=26 April 2020 |publisher=[[Asian News International]]}}</ref>\n\n== References ==    \n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.cisf.gov.in/ Official website of CISF]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Central Industrial Security Force]]\n[[Category:1990 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Police academies in India]]\n[[Category:Ministry of Home Affairs (India)]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Hyderabad, India]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|CISF institute}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name                    = National Industrial Security Academy\n| image                   = \n| alt                     = \n| caption                 = \n| motto                   = <!-- or | mottoes = -->\n| motto_translation       = \n| location                = [[Hakimpet]], [[Medchal\u2013Malkajgiri District]], [[Telangana]]\n| country                 = India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|17|32|29|N|78|31|59|E|display=inline.title}}\n| other_name              = <!-- or | other_names = -->\n| former_name             = <!-- or | former_names = -->\n| type                    = Industrial security academy\n| religio